<div class="BlockPadding" id="experiences">
    <h2 class="subheaders">Author's Personal Experience</h2>
    <br />
    <p class="text">
        "My name is Gracyn Green, and I'm a current student at the University of Nebraska-Lincoln. I chose to major in computer science and it was the best
        decision I've made. However, during my first few courses I did have a feeling of imposter syndrome. I didn't believe I was ready or qualified
        to be in this major when I didn't have extensive knowledge like the rest of the male students in my classes I thought had. It made me question
        why I was here in the first place. Though as I learned more and kept at it, I could see how much I was changing - both in my skill set and in
        my confidence. This semester for my English paper I interviewed someone, and she told me some good advice - "Don't Apologize."
        It's simple but powerful. I was always saying things that made me put to question my skills. It even encouraged my imposter syndrome mindset.
        But I realize and fully believe it now that I am here because I'm meant to be here. I belong to this major and this field just like anyone else.
        I am willing to stand up for myself and make my voice heard. I am a woman in tech and I am not afraid to show that." 
    </p>
